content:
Managing OmniScripts

Export OmniScripts: Export scripts in a DataPack to share with other Salesforce orgs.

Import OmniScripts: Add existing scripts by importing them with a DataPack.

Version OmniScripts: Create multiple versions for development and testing before activating scripts for production deployment.

Emailing an OmniScript: Use Integration Procedures to send links to contacts, leads, or users.

Version OmniScript allows creating multiple versions of a script. 

Importing and exporting OmniScripts allow adding or sharing scripts between orgs.
title: Managing OmniScripts in Salesforce
